fields.Action:
1. Initiate a CWMP session
2. The ACS issues a Reboot RPC
fields.Expected Result:
To be successful, the following must happen:
1. The device must send a RebootResponse
2. The CWMP session must continue and eventually be successfully terminated
3. The device must actually reboot
4. The device must initiate a CWMP session. The Inform must contain both the “1 BOOT” and “M Reboot” events and the command key for the “M Reboot” event must match the message ID specified in the original Reboot request.

the 1 BOOT must include the following parameters:
{code:java}
Device.RootDataModelVersion
Device.DeviceInfo.Manufacturer
Device.DeviceInfo.ManufacturerOUI
Device.DeviceInfo.ModelName
Device.DeviceInfo.ProductClass
Device.DeviceInfo.SerialNumber
Device.DeviceInfo.HardwareVersion
Device.DeviceInfo.SoftwareVersion
Device.DeviceInfo.ProvisioningCode
Device.DeviceInfo.UpTime
Device.ManagementServer.ParameterKey
Device.ManagementServer.ConnectionRequestURL
Device.IP.Interface.{i}.IPv4Address.{i}.IPAddress
Device.Services.X_VZ-COM_DeviceConfig.WanType
Device.Services.X_VZ-COM_DeviceConfig.WanMAC
Device.ManagementServer.AliasBasedAddressing

Device.Services.X_VZ-COM_DeviceConfig.X509Cert.RetryEnabled
Device.Services.X_VZ-COM_DeviceConfig.X509Cert.RetryCounter
Device.Services.X_VZ-COM_DeviceConfig.X509Cert.SCEPReportStatus
Device.Services.X_VZ-COM_DeviceConfig.X509Cert.ClientSCEPStatus
Device.Services.X_VZ-COM_DeviceConfig.SHP.Enabled
Device.Services.X_VZ-COM_DeviceConfig.BDCS.Enable

Device.Services.X_VZ-COM_DeviceConfig.DNSRebindProtection.Enable
Device.IP.Interface.{i}.IPv6Address.{i}.IPAddress
